<Layouts.flash_group flash={@flash} />

<div class="sq-page min-h-screen">
    <div class="sq-shell mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-6 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <header
            class="sq-nav flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-[2rem] px-5 py-4 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between sm:px-6">
            <div>
                <p class="sq-eyebrow">Civio access tracking</p>
                <a href="#top" class="sq-brand mt-1 inline-flex items-center gap-3 text-2xl font-semibold">
                    <span class="sq-logo-mark">S</span>
                    SQLete
                </a>
            </div>

            <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 sm:justify-end">
                <nav class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 text-sm text-base-content/70">
                    <a href="#que-hace" class="sq-nav-link">Que hacemos</a>
                    <a href="#como-funciona" class="sq-nav-link">Como funciona</a>
                    <a href="#impacto" class="sq-nav-link">Impacto</a>
                </nav>
                <Layouts.theme_toggle />
            </div>
        </header>

        <main id="top" class="space-y-8 py-8 sm:space-y-10 sm:py-10">
            <section class="sq-hero grid gap-8 rounded-[2rem] px-6 py-10 lg:grid-cols-[1.2fr_0.8fr] lg:px-10 lg:py-12">
                <div class="space-y-6">
                    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 text-sm font-medium">
                        <span class="sq-pill">Phoenix + LiveView</span>
                        <span class="sq-pill">LLM document parsing</span>
                        <span class="sq-pill">Deadline engine</span>
                    </div>

                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <p class="sq-eyebrow">Hackathon landing page</p>
                        <h1 class="sq-display max-w-3xl text-4xl leading-none sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
                            The inbox for transparency requests that should not be managed in spreadsheets.
                        </h1>
                        <p class="max-w-2xl text-base leading-7 text-base-content/75 sm:text-lg">
                            SQLete turns opaque PDF notifications into structured case tracking. Drop a document,
                            identify the response, calculate legal deadlines, and surface the files that need action
                            before they expire.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
                        <a href="#que-hace" class="btn sq-button-primary">See what we automate</a>
                        <a href="#como-funciona" class="btn btn-ghost sq-button-secondary">Review the workflow</a>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="grid gap-4 self-start">
                    <article class="sq-highlight-card rounded-[1.75rem] p-5">
                        <p class="sq-card-label">Main promise</p>
                        <p class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold leading-tight">
                            One notification in, deadlines and case status out.
                        </p>
                        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-base-content/70">
                            The app classifies the PDF, extracts dates, updates the request, and marks whether the team
                            needs to claim silence, review an incomplete answer, or follow a redistributed file.
                        </p>
                    </article>

                    <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
                        <article class="sq-stat-card rounded-[1.5rem] p-5">
                            <p class="sq-card-label">Input</p>
                            <p class="mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold">PDF drag and drop</p>
                            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-base-content/70">Manual upload, no scraping, no digital
                                certificate in scope.</p>
                        </article>

                        <article class="sq-stat-card rounded-[1.5rem] p-5">
                            <p class="sq-card-label">Output</p>
                            <p class="mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold">Daily legal radar</p>
                            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-base-content/70">Red-zone deadlines, grouped files, and a digest
                                the team can trust.</p>
                        </article>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section id="que-hace" class="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-3">
                <article class="sq-panel rounded-[1.75rem] p-6">
                    <p class="sq-card-label">01. Interpret notifications</p>
                    <h2 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold">Read the document, not just the filename</h2>
                    <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-base-content/75">
                        We detect whether the PDF is a start of processing, an extension, a partial response, or a
                        denial, and we extract the dates that actually drive the case.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="sq-panel rounded-[1.75rem] p-6">
                    <p class="sq-card-label">02. Compute deadlines</p>
                    <h2 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold">Apply the legal clock automatically</h2>
                    <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-base-content/75">
                        SQLete calculates normal deadlines, article 20.1 extensions, negative silence windows, and CTBG
                        claim deadlines without storing duplicated spreadsheet formulas.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="sq-panel rounded-[1.75rem] p-6">
                    <p class="sq-card-label">03. Spot redistribution</p>
                    <h2 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold">Follow one request across many files</h2>
                    <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-base-content/75">
                        Related references in notes and future grouping rules let the newsroom see when a single request
                        has been split into many parallel case files.
                    </p>
                </article>
            </section>

            <section id="como-funciona" class="sq-panel rounded-[2rem] px-6 py-8 sm:px-8 lg:px-10">
                <div class="max-w-3xl">
                    <p class="sq-eyebrow">How it works</p>
                    <h2 class="sq-section-title mt-3 text-3xl sm:text-4xl">A simple workflow for a high-friction process
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-base leading-7 text-base-content/75">
                        The product is designed around the real Civio process: a journalist receives a notification,
                        opens a PDF, figures out what happened, updates the tracker by hand, and recalculates every
                        deadline. SQLete compresses that into one pass.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="mt-8 grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-4">
                    <article class="sq-step-card rounded-[1.5rem] p-5">
                        <p class="sq-step-number">1</p>
                        <h3 class="mt-4 text-lg font-semibold">Upload the PDF</h3>
                        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-base-content/70">The newsroom drops the official document
                            into the app instead of parsing it by hand.</p>
                    </article>

                    <article class="sq-step-card rounded-[1.5rem] p-5">
                        <p class="sq-step-number">2</p>
                        <h3 class="mt-4 text-lg font-semibold">Validate structured data</h3>
                        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-base-content/70">The LLM returns typed fields so the
                            system can create or update the matching request safely.</p>
                    </article>

                    <article class="sq-step-card rounded-[1.5rem] p-5">
                        <p class="sq-step-number">3</p>
                        <h3 class="mt-4 text-lg font-semibold">Recalculate legal status</h3>
                        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-base-content/70">Deadline rules run immediately and
                            identify whether action is required today, this week, or next month.</p>
                    </article>

                    <article class="sq-step-card rounded-[1.5rem] p-5">
                        <p class="sq-step-number">4</p>
                        <h3 class="mt-4 text-lg font-semibold">Surface the urgent cases</h3>
                        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-base-content/70">The dashboard and digest show what is
                            expiring, what is blocked, and what has spread into multiple files.</p>
                    </article>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section id="impacto" class="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-[0.9fr_1.1fr]">
                <article class="sq-panel rounded-[2rem] p-6 sm:p-8">
                    <p class="sq-eyebrow">Why it matters</p>
                    <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold leading-tight">Less detective work, fewer missed deadlines,
                        clearer editorial follow-up.</h2>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-base-content/75">
                        The goal is not generic document AI. It is a newsroom operations tool for one specific problem:
                        keeping public-information requests alive long enough to get an answer worth publishing.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
                    <article class="sq-stat-card rounded-[1.5rem] p-6">
                        <p class="sq-card-label">Real data model</p>
                        <p class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold">Seeded from Civio CSV</p>
                        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-base-content/70">The first version mirrors the existing
                            Airtable fields so the team can migrate without rethinking its whole workflow.</p>
                    </article>

                    <article class="sq-stat-card rounded-[1.5rem] p-6">
                        <p class="sq-card-label">Safe AI scope</p>
                        <p class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold">Classification and extraction only</p>
                        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-base-content/70">No generated legal writing, no portal
                            scraping, and no outbound communication. The AI is constrained to internal operational
                            tasks.</p>
                    </article>

                    <article class="sq-stat-card rounded-[1.5rem] p-6 sm:col-span-2">
                        <p class="sq-card-label">What comes next</p>
                        <p class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold">This page is the starting point for the dashboard, case
                            detail, and grouped redistribution views.</p>
                        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-base-content/70">
                            For now the landing page explains the product clearly. The next slices can add the actual
                            dashboard routes without redoing the visual system.
                        </p>
                    </article>
                </div>
            </section>
        </main>
    </div>
</div>